                <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
                <p>At Pehchan, we believe your identity belongs to you. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, process, and safeguard your information when you use our secure authentication application.</p>

                <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>We collect only the information necessary to provide our core identity services. When you log in using Google OAuth, we securely receive and store:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Profile Data:</strong> Your Display Name and Profile Image URL.</li>
                    <li><strong>Contact Data:</strong> Your primary Email Address (e.g., Gmail).</li>
                    <li><strong>Authentication Data:</strong> Unique User IDs generated by Google and Firebase Authentication.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We <strong>do not</strong> access your Google account passwords, emails, contacts, or any other restricted scopes.</p>

                <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>Your data is used strictly for the following purposes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>To create and manage your Pehchan digital identity.</li>
                    <li>To authenticate your sessions securely.</li>
                    <li>To personalize your in-app experience (e.g., displaying your avatar).</li>
                    <li>To maintain account security and prevent fraudulent sign-ups.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
                <p>We utilize <strong>Google Firebase</strong> infrastructure (Firebase Authentication and Cloud Firestore) to store and process your data. Firebase adheres to rigorous global security standards. Your authentication tokens are handled natively and securely on your device and are never exposed to our internal servers in plaintext.</p>

